A one-day Football Coaching Clinic packaged by Carl Academy and Football College , Umuahia for Grassroots coaches in Abia State and its environs is on now at the academy,National Daily learnt.

The Clinic, with the theme,” Technical and Tactical Development ” was declared open by the Abia State Commissioner for Sports, Dr Martins Okoji, represented by the Director of Information in the ministry, and Abia SWAN Chairman Prince Vincent Obike.

Former Super Eagles captain, Peter Rufai is the resource person and he poured encomiums on Pastor Emeka Inyama, the brain behind Carl Academy and Football College and the Coaching Clinic for his courage and hoped it will impact tremendously on society.
